{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"67cf9e31-d182-4463-a7e9-1be9fa768f4f","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01GnBx9t66Anyn5rnSPAg3id","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013iBSCxHkdUKmvvyAZx4QdN","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"dotnet --version 2>/dev/null; dotnet nuget list source 2>/dev/null | head -5","description":"Check .NET SDK version and NuGet sources","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check .NET SDK version and NuGet sources"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01LhkpUANFLBTvmPyXcdstn8","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/xunit.v3/index.json","max_length":2000},"type":"function","toolTitle":"Fetching web content","intentionSummary":"https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/xunit.v3/index.json"}],"interactionId":"a38c92db-0067-4480-93e1-504a1cbc0ee1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me migrate from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3. Key changes needed:\n\n1. **Project file (TestProject.csproj)**:\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` and `xunit.runner.visualstudio` packages\n   - Replace `xunit` v2 with `xunit.v3` v3\n   - Change SDK from `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` (stays the same, but need to add output type)\n   - In xUnit v3, test projects are executables, not libraries. Need `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`\n   - The built-in runner handles test execution, so I don't need the separate test SDK or Visual Studio runner packages\n   - Tests must use `async Task` instead of `async void`, and the test project itself becomes an executable with its own entry point\n   - For `dotnet test` compatibility, you can still add `xunit.runner.visualstudio` v3, but the core `xunit.v3` package includes everything needed for the in-process runner\n   - The main package `xunit.v3` bundles assertions, core functionality, and the runner together, so you don't need `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` separately\n   - Test projects need `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` to run as standalone executables\n\nNow I'm working through the migration steps: converting `async void` test methods to `async Task` since xUnit v3 forbids void async tests, and checking what runner configuration changes are needed in the project setup. The package structure for xUnit v3 includes the main meta-package along with specialized sub-packages, and for Visual Studio Test runner integration I'd need `xunit.runner.visualstudio` version 3.x. Since xUnit v3 embeds the runner in the project itself, making it executable is possible, but `dotnet test` integration still requires an adapter. Let me proceed with setting this up. I need to update the project file to switch to xunit.v3 and remove the test runner packages, then convert the async void method to async Task. I should also check what .NET SDK version is available to ensure compatibility.","outputTokens":1880,"requestId":"4818:1E31:FB4C82:11E2BE1:69FBEEBE"},"id":"e1ecf55a-21dc-4589-9e57-aff9bad20f1c","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:46:10.173Z","parentId":"19f74f56-86b8-40ff-9953-7b962ec8d62b"}
